This paper deals with the problem of estimating machine learning performance, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the statistical rigor of the proposed method, which could also fall under the sub-field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
